narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I gained a great deal of knowledge about Asian American history. I also learned a lot about different approaches and trends within historiography.

This course was really helpful in terms of learning how to read a book and dissect it for key dates and timelines. I feel like my grasp on the material we read is far more grounded and nuanced than in other classes I have taken.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: We read so many different texts, which I really appreciate! That said, it felt like there wasn't enough time to read more -- I would have loved further discussion on some of the more recent trends within Asian Am Studies.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: This class provides a great foundation for Asian Am scholars.
Absolutely. One of the other helpful aspects of this course was Professor Lui's comments on our responses-- they really pushed me to think about how and why I am writing.
